text: Knut Sven-Erik Magnusson (13 October 1942 â€“ 22 March 2017) was a Swedish singer and musician. He was known for being the lead singer of the danceband Sven-Ingvars. The band had its last tour during the summer of 2016 with their last show on 21 August in Blekinge. He was born in Slottsbron, Sweden. Magnusson died on 22 March 2017 of prostate cancer in Karlstad, Sweden, aged 74. ==References== ==Other websites== Category:1942 births Category:2017 deaths Category:Deaths from prostate cancer Category:Cancer deaths in Sweden Category:Swedish singers Category:Swedish guitarists Category:Saxophonists Category:Clarinetists
